  <title>MyWalletWatcher ERD</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h2>Datasets</h2>
  <p>MyWalletWatcher utilizes three primary data sources to comprehensively manage personal finances:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>CSV Spreadsheets:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Populates initial datasets for <code>accounts</code>, <code>household_members</code>, <code>categories</code>, and <code>tags</code>.</li>
        <li>Represents foundational financial accounts, household members, and transaction categories/tags.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li><strong>Faker Gem:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Generates 200 synthetic records for the <code>transactions</code> table.</li>
        <li>Ensures a diverse dataset for testing and development purposes.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li><strong>CRUD Functionality:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Empowers users to interactively manage financial information.</li>
        <li>Allows Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations for a dynamic user experience.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Entity-Relationship Diagram (ERD)</h2>
  <figure class="figure">
    <%= image_tag('erd.jpg', alt: 'ERD', style: 'width: 80%; height: auto;') %>
  </figure>
  <p>
    This diagram illustrates the relationships between different models in our database.
  </p>
</body>
</html>
